    "type": "message",
    "subtype": "thread_broadcast",
    "text": "I'm thinking this is too good a thread to drop or have limited visibility, so I'm re-energising it!\n\nI've been digging into Raskin's work this morning; here are some links I found:\n\n<https://www.wired.com/1993/06/1-6-guis/>\n<https://web.archive.org/web/20080509155848/http://jef.raskincenter.org/humane_interface/summary_of_thi.html>\n<https://wiki.c2.com/?TheHumaneInterface>\n<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Archy_(software)>",
    "user": "UE6EFEPTQ",
    "ts": "1707900486.134759",
    "thread_ts": "1700506589.079709",
    "root": {
      "type": "message",
      "text": "I was leafing through my father's old books when this diagram caught me off-guard.\nWe're so used now to having an OS with apps, that it's weird to think of OS-level transitions (login-&gt;shell), inter-apps transitions (shell-&gt;vi) and inside-app transitions (vi's command&lt;-&gt;append modes) as similar things. :upside_down_face:\nBut to a user new to computers, yes these are all \"modes\".",
      "files": [
        {
          "id": "F066D6FURRU",
          "mode": "hidden_by_limit"
        }
      ],
      "upload": false,
      "user": "U02QC0PPER3",
      "display_as_bot": false,
      "ts": "1700506589.079709",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "block_id": "kczXV",
          "elements": [
            {
              "type": "rich_text_section",
              "elements": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "I was leafing through my father's old books when this diagram caught me off-guard.\nWe're so used now to having an OS with apps, that it's weird to think of OS-level transitions (login->shell), inter-apps transitions (shell->vi) and inside-app transitions (vi's command<->append modes) as similar things. "
                },
                {
                  "type": "emoji",
                  "name": "upside_down_face",
                  "unicode": "1f643"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "\nBut to a user new to computers, yes these are all \"modes\"."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
